107.8	Will_Wright_(game_designer)	Will Wright (game designer)	William Ralph "Will" Wright (born January 20, 1960, in Atlanta, Georgia) is an American video game designer and co-founder of the game development company Maxis, now part of Electronic Arts. In April 2009, he left Electronic Arts to run "Stupid Fun Club", an entertainment think tank in which Wright and EA are principal shareholders.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Will_Wright_-_Game_Developers_Conference_2010_%282%29.jpg/220px-Will_Wright_-_Game_Developers_Conference_2010_%282%29.jpg
